<sec>
<st>
 Panama disease </st>
<p>

<b>Panama disease</b>, also known as <b>Fusarium wilt</b>, is a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../940/38940.xml">
banana</link> <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../484/147484.xml">
plant disease</link> caused by the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../965/19178965.xml">
fungus</link> <it><link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../937/312937.xml">
Fusarium oxysporum</link></it>. The fungus attacks the roots of the banana plant. The disease is resistant to <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../758/515758.xml">
fungicide</link> and, so, cannot be controlled chemically.</p>

